  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies a design coordinate value for a single variation axis of a variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate` pairs an axis tag with a design value and is used
to specify the exact position along each variable font axis when cloning a typeface.
Pass a span of these values to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.VariationDesignPosition> or directly to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate})>.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var coords = new[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
    {
        Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"),
        Value = 700f,
    },
};
using var bold = typeface.Clone(coords);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
